The Straits Times and the National Library Board you ask, we answer, come listen Home-based food businesses Singapore has always had home-based food businesses. But during the circuit breaker, they mushroomed like never before. Out-of-work Singaporea­ns started selling food from home to earn an income, others to supplement their pay. Now, they are a force to be reckoned with. How do these businesses evolve? Tan Hsueh Yun Come listen to food editor as she shares her thoughts on this new force to be reckoned with, and what the future holds for these businesses. Watch the video The Straits Times www.facebook.com/ TheStraits­Times Today at 7pm With guest speakers Tan Hsueh Yun Food Editor
